    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Fear attacks can have various effects.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Fear Aura (Su):</em> The use of this ability is a free action. The aura can freeze an opponent (as in the case of a <a href=\"https://www.aonprd.com/MonsterDisplay.aspx?ItemName=Mummy\">mummy&rsquo;s despair</a>) or function like the <a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; background-image: none; background-color: initial; padding: 0px; color: #ff6400; border: none;\" draggable=\"false\" data-pack=\"pf1.spells\" data-id=\"be88e90guqbi1q1z\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; text-decoration-line: underline;\">fear</span></a> spell. Other effects are possible. A fear aura is an area effect. The descriptive text gives the size and kind of the area.</p>\n<p><em>Fear Cone (Sp) and Ray (Su):</em> These effects usually work like the <a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; background-image: none; background-color: initial; padding: 0px; color: #ff6400; border: none;\" draggable=\"false\" data-pack=\"pf1.spells\" data-id=\"be88e90guqbi1q1z\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; text-decoration-line: underline;\">fear</span></a> spell. If a fear effect allows a saving throw, it is a Will save (DC = 10 + 1/2 the fearsome creature&rsquo;s racial HD + that creature&rsquo;s Charisma modifier; the exact DC is given in the creature&rsquo;s descriptive text). All fear attacks are mind-affecting fear effects.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Format</em>: fear aura (30 ft., DC 17) <em>or</em> fear cone (50 ft., DC 19)</p>\n<p><em>Location</em>: Aura <em>or</em> Special Attacks.</p>",
